1
00:00:00,060 --> 00:00:02,190
So you wanna make $10,000 a month,

2
00:00:02,190 --> 00:00:04,230
but you don't know which route to take?

3
00:00:04,230 --> 00:00:06,390
Most people take the traditional route.

4
00:00:06,390 --> 00:00:10,020
They go to school, study
hard for their exams,

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,930
get good grades, go to university,

6
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:15,060
and then get a nine to five job.

7
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:17,700
Sorry to burst your bubble,
but the average person

8
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,700
makes $63,795 per year
according to the latest data

9
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:25,500
from the Social Security Administration.

10
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,920
That's $5,316 per month,

11
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,980
so nowhere near your
goal of $10,000 a month.

12
00:00:31,980 --> 00:00:34,320
Even worse, this data includes people

13
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:36,060
who've been in the game for ages.

14
00:00:36,060 --> 00:00:38,460
So if you're just
starting out in your 20s,

15
00:00:38,460 --> 00:00:41,550
you'll probably be making
way less than 5K a month

16
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:43,650
if you stick to this old school path.

17
00:00:43,650 --> 00:00:46,320
But hey, let's say somehow
you hit the jackpot

18
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:49,680
and score a nine to five gig
that pays you 10K a month.

19
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:52,200
Maybe you become a
hotshot doctor or lawyer.

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:55,080
Sounds great, right? Well, not so fast.

21
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,700
You'd still be trading away your time

22
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,260
and freedom for that paycheck.

23
00:00:58,260 --> 00:01:01,440
This was the route that my
parents expected me to follow.

24
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,920
They believed it was the
only way to a secure future.

25
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:06,840
Maybe some of you're
sitting there right now

26
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:09,510
feeling that same
pressure with your parents

27
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:10,950
expecting the same of you.

28
00:01:10,950 --> 00:01:14,190
However, deep down you feel
like there must be a faster way

29
00:01:14,190 --> 00:01:17,490
you can make over 10K per
month with more freedom,

30
00:01:17,490 --> 00:01:21,390
and that's exactly where
the new route comes in.

31
00:01:21,390 --> 00:01:22,260
Don't worry.

32
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,940
I know this sounds like it's leading up

33
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:25,200
to some sort of sales pitch,

34
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,030
but I'm not gonna try
and sell you anything,

35
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,950
so feel free to relax.

36
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:31,410
You can follow this route
completely for free,

37
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:33,930
and how you navigate
it will depend on you.

38
00:01:33,930 --> 00:01:37,380
Many successful people like
Steven Bartlett, Joe Fazer,

39
00:01:37,380 --> 00:01:40,020
and Ali Abdaal are taking
this route already,

40
00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:42,270
but they aren't really talking about it.

41
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:43,850
It also doesn't matter how old you are

42
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:46,830
as you can switch to this new
route, no matter what stage

43
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:48,810
of the traditional route
you're currently on.

44
00:01:48,810 --> 00:01:50,400
However, the longer you wait,

45
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,010
the tougher it gets to make that big jump.

46
00:01:53,010 --> 00:01:53,843
Why?

47
00:01:53,843 --> 00:01:56,430
Well, as you keep going
down this usual path,

48
00:01:56,430 --> 00:01:58,440
life starts piling on more stuff,

49
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:00,660
you know, like a mortgage, a partner,

50
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:02,400
kids, the whole shebang.

51
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:05,460
Don't get me wrong, you can
still switch gears at any stage,

52
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:07,470
but trust me, it's way easier

53
00:02:07,470 --> 00:02:09,600
if you do it sooner rather than later.

54
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,480
I left school with no
money or qualification,

55
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:15,150
so I was forced down this route early on,

56
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:17,280
and I believe that's
one of the key reasons

57
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:19,470
I became a millionaire in my 20s

58
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:22,200
and have been able to compound
that wealth ever since.

59
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,450
Hopefully, you are convinced
that this new route

60
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:26,850
to making over $10,000 per month

61
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:28,590
is at least worth learning about.

62
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:31,440
So let me break down the
three steps involved.

63
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,360
Step one is consume.

64
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,910
Believe it or not, you
don't know everything.

65
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:39,120
If you think you do, then
you're delusional and arrogant.

66
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,160
So what's the solution to this?

67
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:43,620
It's simple, consuming knowledge.

68
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:44,880
Think of it this way.

69
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,760
It's like gathering
resources in Minecraft.

70
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:49,830
You need the right materials to build,

71
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:52,260
survive, and ultimately conquer.

72
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:55,170
However, the education
system never really teach you

73
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:57,660
how to find information worth consuming.

74
00:02:57,660 --> 00:03:00,180
It's not as simple as
reading boring textbook

75
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,920
or a quick Google search.

76
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,300
So here's some advice.

77
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:05,520
Before you even reach for your laptop,

78
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,070
you need to identify
what you want to learn.

79
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:10,920
This needs to be some
kind of high income skill.

80
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,560
Some examples that come
to mind are video editing,

81
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,410
high ticket sales, web design, coding,

82
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:18,570
graphic design, and copywriting.

83
00:03:18,570 --> 00:03:20,880
Honestly, there are so many out there.

84
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,110
Just pick one that you feel

85
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:24,960
you'd already have a little
bit of a natural gift for.

86
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,330
It's always easier to sharpen a strength

87
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:28,710
and develop a weakness.

88
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:30,120
Once you've narrowed it down,

89
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,430
this area will become your focus.

90
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:35,310
Now you need time to seek
out credible sources.

91
00:03:35,310 --> 00:03:36,360
I know I'm biased,

92
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:39,480
but I think the best place
to do this is on YouTube.

93
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,870
Find some trustworthy
experts with large audiences.

94
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:46,140
Watch their videos and
note down their key points.

95
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:48,540
You need to extract the key information,

96
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,520
not copy down their life story.

97
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:54,390
Ask yourself, what point is
that person actually making,

98
00:03:54,390 --> 00:03:57,180
and what lesson is behind
their story or experience?

99
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,550
Once you've done that and
your notes are looking solid,

100
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:02,130
I'd start to look at the types
of people that are watching

101
00:04:02,130 --> 00:04:04,110
and engaging with that content.

102
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,420
If you notice they have
a strong community,

103
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:07,860
then get stuck in.

104
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:09,120
I'd even go the extra mile

105
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:11,100
and head over to Reddit and Discord.

106
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:13,200
This way, you'll be able
to connect with people

107
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,870
that are passionate about
the same niche as you.

108
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,880
Engage with them, ask questions,

109
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,620
and learn from their experiences.

110
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:22,230
I guarantee you, joining
these types of groups

111
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:23,640
will give you a proper insight

112
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:26,340
into the real struggles
that people are facing,

113
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:27,690
which is far more valuable

114
00:04:27,690 --> 00:04:29,970
than watching only the creators' videos.

115
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:32,850
It's one thing to learn
from top creators online,

116
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:34,830
but when you dive into these communities,

117
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:38,190
you get a front row seat to
see what's really going on,

118
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:40,470
giving you access to priceless knowledge.

119
00:04:40,470 --> 00:04:43,710
Trust me, this will come
in very handy later on.

120
00:04:43,710 --> 00:04:46,170
A word of warning, though,
it can be very easy

121
00:04:46,170 --> 00:04:49,080
to fall into the trap of
only watching one person

122
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,690
or even just watching YouTube videos.

123
00:04:51,690 --> 00:04:53,190
If you wanna get the most from this,

124
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:55,470
then you need to be
consuming from a variety

125
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:57,450
of different people and mediums.

126
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:58,440
In other words,

127
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:00,660
you really shouldn't be
shying away from books.

128
00:05:00,660 --> 00:05:02,520
I'm a huge fan of books.

129
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:05,610
They're like a shortcut to
someone's entire life experience,

130
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:08,970
but I'm dyslexic, so
plowing through a whole book

131
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:10,710
can be a real pain sometimes.

132
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:13,020
That's why I'm all about
these Shortform guides.

133
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:15,180
For me, Shortform is the go-to

134
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:18,390
for diving deep into books
like "The Intelligent Investor"

135
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:20,610
and gaining in-depth insights.

136
00:05:20,610 --> 00:05:22,620
They're the best summary service out there

137
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:24,150
and let me learn from five books

138
00:05:24,150 --> 00:05:25,710
in the time it takes to read one.

139
00:05:25,710 --> 00:05:27,780
I'll drop a link in the
description that you can use

140
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:30,030
to try it for free and get 20% off.

141
00:05:30,030 --> 00:05:31,770
Step two is apply.

142
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:32,820
If you wanna get rich,

143
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:35,370
then you have to apply
the things you consume.

144
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:36,660
This is super important,

145
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:38,520
is you need to get out
there in the real world

146
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:39,840
and test what you've learned.

147
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:43,260
The best way to do this
is to consume, then apply,

148
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,720
consume some more, and then apply again.

149
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,280
It's a cycle that only stops

150
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,990
when you want to stop progressing.

151
00:05:48,990 --> 00:05:52,050
Let's say you've decided to
consume content on coding.

152
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:54,870
Now is the time to make
your first simple app.

153
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:56,070
It sounds daunting,

154
00:05:56,070 --> 00:05:59,520
and at first you're probably
gonna suck, but that's okay.

155
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,830
You've got to give yourself
permission to fail.

156
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:03,870
Mark Zuckerberg didn't create Facebook

157
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:05,280
for his first project.

158
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,950
JK Rowling got rejected 12 times

159
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:10,170
before she published "Harry Potter."

160
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:12,510
And Beyonce made hundreds of songs

161
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:13,980
before her first smash hit.

162
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:16,057
In the words of Mark Zuckerberg himself,

163
00:06:16,057 --> 00:06:17,730
"The greatest successes

164
00:06:17,730 --> 00:06:19,800
come from having the freedom to fail."

165
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,600
As soon as you feel confident enough,

166
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,880
start charging for your skills.

167
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,050
If you edit videos,

168
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:28,110
then take on a few lower
paying clients at first

169
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:29,430
and work your way up.

170
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:30,960
Just think, all you need to do

171
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,930
is get five clients paying $2,000 a month

172
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:36,810
or 10 clients paying $1,000 a month

173
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:38,520
for your video editing services,

174
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:41,610
and you've already hit
the 10K per month target.

175
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:44,340
The better you get, the more
you'll be able to charge

176
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:47,340
and the easier it will be
to make more and more money.

177
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:50,250
However, this is a game
of diminishing returns,

178
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:53,070
meaning the hours you put in
learning the skill at the start

179
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,990
will have more impact on your income

180
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:56,610
than the hours later down the line.

181
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:59,190
It's like when you first
start to work out of the gym,

182
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:01,170
you get newbie gains.

183
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:04,050
It's best to consume and apply
until you get to the point

184
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,940
where you aren't noticing an increase

185
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:08,370
in the amount you're able
to charge for your services.

186
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:09,600
This is how you know

187
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,450
you've reached pretty much expert status.

188
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:14,520
During this time, make sure to keep note

189
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:18,300
of all the challenges you face
and problems you overcome.

190
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,560
These will become stories

191
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,690
you can draw on heavily in the future.

192
00:07:21,690 --> 00:07:24,540
Believe it or not, during the apply stage,

193
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:27,360
the most important thing
you'll gain isn't the money,

194
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,640
but instead the experiences themselves.

195
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:32,490
Once you're an expert in a
specific high income skill,

196
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:34,410
it can be very easy to get stuck here,

197
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:38,190
trading every hour you
have to earn 10K per month.

198
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:40,590
But remember, the goal isn't to reach 10K

199
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:42,210
and lose all your freedom.

200
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:45,090
So instead, I recommend
doing these two things.

201
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:47,700
Firstly, start to scale
your high income skill

202
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,260
into a real business.

203
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,960
I know you might be thinking,
"It's already a business,"

204
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:54,720
but if you have to be
working to generate income,

205
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:57,690
then the truth is, you just
have a high paying job.

206
00:07:57,690 --> 00:07:59,700
So how can you scale a high income skill

207
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:01,500
into a proper business?

208
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,940
Well, I know a guy

209
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:05,790
that started editing shorts for YouTubers.

210
00:08:05,790 --> 00:08:07,980
He was working every hour under the sun.

211
00:08:07,980 --> 00:08:10,230
However, one day he just got fed up

212
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:11,730
with working all the time

213
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:14,100
and not having the
freedom to take vacations,

214
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:17,010
so he started to note down
all the steps he would take

215
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:19,920
to make the shorts, from the
way he selected the clips

216
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,180
to the font he used

217
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:24,330
and the time of day he
posted at the social media.

218
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:27,840
He didn't know it at the time,
but he was creating a system.

219
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,270
He realized that he wasn't
gonna be able to find someone

220
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:32,400
to do all the tasks like him.

221
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:35,640
However, he could split the
tasks into separate jobs,

222
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:39,060
such as time stamper,
text editor, and poster.

223
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:41,580
This way he could find
far less skilled people

224
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:43,260
to fill in the roles for him

225
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:45,600
so he could focus on the quality control

226
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,160
and take on more clients.

227
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,560
You can do this with
any high income skill.

228
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:51,990
The system will also become super useful

229
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,510
for the next thing I
highly recommend doing,

230
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:56,910
teaching others your high income skill.

231
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:59,670
That brings me on to step three, educate.

232
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,020
Most of the young millionaires

233
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:02,580
that have gained success recently

234
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,890
have made their fortunes teaching others.

235
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:07,560
I'm talking Iman Gadzhi, Ali Abdaal,

236
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,750
Graham Stephan, the list goes on.

237
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,030
The education industry is booming,

238
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:14,160
and I believe everyone making decent money

239
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,470
from some kind of high income skill

240
00:09:16,470 --> 00:09:18,690
should also have an education business.

241
00:09:18,690 --> 00:09:21,240
I mean, just imagine you created a course

242
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,980
that you sold for $100.

243
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:23,910
All you'd have to do

244
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:26,400
is sell that course 100 times in a month

245
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,470
and you'd hit that 10K per month.

246
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:30,600
The great thing is you
only have to make it once

247
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,640
and then you can sell it again and again,

248
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,590
getting your freedom and time back.

249
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:38,040
Education products don't just
have to be online courses.

250
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:40,950
You could also start
exclusive membership sites,

251
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:43,410
subscription podcasts, communities,

252
00:09:43,410 --> 00:09:45,390
personalized coaching, and more.

253
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:48,330
These types of businesses
are extremely cost effective

254
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:49,710
to set up and run.

255
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:52,770
They also have the upside
of being extremely scalable

256
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:55,530
as they generate predictable,
reoccurring revenue.

